goals.question: What is the distribution of wildlife species involved in aircraft incidents?
goals.rationale: This helps identify the most common wildlife species involved in aircraft incidents, which can inform decisions on how to prevent such incidents.

goals.question: What is the distribution of aircraft makes and models involved in incidents?

goals.question: What is the distribution of the effect amount of damage caused by wildlife strikes?

goals.question: What is the distribution of the phase of flight during which incidents occur?
goals.rationale: This helps identify the most common phases of flight during which incidents occur, which can inform decisions on safety measures and training for pilots and crew.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    species_count = data['Wildlife_Species'].value_counts()
    species_count.plot(kind='bar', color='c', legend=True)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wildlife species involved in aircraft incidents?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Wildlife Species')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Incidents')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    aircraft_counts = data['Aircraft_Make_Model'].value_counts()
    aircraft_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='blue', legend=True)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of aircraft makes and models involved in incidents?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Aircraft Make and Model')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Incidents')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'].plot(kind='hist', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the effect amount of damage caused by wildlife strikes?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Effect Amount of Damage')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.axvline(data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.title('What is the distribution of the phase of flight during which incidents occur?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Phase of Flight')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Incidents')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['Cost_Total__'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(data['Cost_Total__'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['Cost_Total__'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Cost_Total__')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the cost of incidents?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
